*******************************************************************************
@NODE OVER "NiGHT-SCANNER v1.OO - Overview"

 NiGHT-SCANNER  is the nocTurne deSign entry into the NewFiles door market.
 It  has  been  merged  with  Files-Reverse  so that it functions as both a
 new-files directory scanner as well as a reverse scanner (showing files in
 their  reverse  chronological  order,  newest   to   oldest).    NS offers
 flexibility  for  both  the sysop and the user.  An easily editable config
 file  allows the operator to define defaults, access levels, graphics, and
 more.    A user config file allows users to customize NS to act and output
 to  their  satisfaction.  Packed with features and conveniences, NS should
 prove  to  be  file-scanning  door to contend with.  Read further for more
 details.

@ENDNODE
*******************************************************************************
@NODE INSTALL "NiGHT-SCANNER v1.O - Installation"

 This program is an XIM and should be installed as such.  Knowledge of door
 installation  convention  is  assumed.   Icons have been provided for 3.xx
 owners.    Note that once installed, NS and its support files should be in
 the  drawer  "DOORS:noC-NS/"  The  text  file  "NS.CONFiG"  allows  you to
 configure the door's various sysop options, which are detailed here:

  ------------------------------------------------------------------------
  @{" DIVIDERS    " LINK TT1 } Divider Lines?  Access Lvl for Hold Dir @{" HOLD.ACS        " LINK TT5 }
  @{" COLORS      " LINK TT2 } Color Display?
  @{" SHOWNEWDATE " LINK TT3 } Date Lines?       Key-Command Full Name @{" KC_NAME.[NUM]   " LINK TT6 }
  @{" FILENUMBERS " LINK TT4 } File Numbering?            KC Door Name @{" KC_CMD.[NUM]    " LINK TT7 }
  @{" DIVIDER.TXT " LINK TT11} Divider Graphic      KC Key Designation @{" KC_KEY.[NUM]    " LINK TT8 }
  @{" NEWDATE.TXT " LINK TT12} Date Graphic        Access Level for KC @{" KC_ACCESS.[NUM] " LINK TT9 }
  @{" ENDLINE.TXT " LINK TT13} Final Graphic       Accept args for KC? @{" KC_ARGS.[NUM]   " LINK TT10 }
  ------------------------------------------------------------------------
@ENDNODE
******************************************************************************
@NODE TT1 "NiGHT-SCANNER v1.O Config Parameter - DIVIDERS"

 @{b}Template: @{ub}DIVIDERS=[YES/NO]
  @{b}Example: @{ub}DIVIDERS=YES

 If  you  want  to  enable  by default the dividing lines between each file
 description, simply set this option to YES.  The text in the "DIVIDER.TXT"
 config parameter will be utilized as the divider graphic.

@ENDNODE
******************************************************************************
@NODE TT2 "NiGHT-SCANNER v1.O Config Parameter - COLORS"

 @{b}Template: @{ub}COLORS=[YES/NO]
  @{b}Example: @{ub}COLORS=YES

 To  make colors in the listing default, set this parameter to YES.  Colors
 will be used in the file number, (if used), and file information.

@ENDNODE
******************************************************************************
@NODE TT3 "NiGHT-SCANNER v1.O Config Parameter - SHOWNEWDATE"

 @{b}Template: @{ub}SHOWNEWDATE=[YES/NO]
  @{b}Example: @{ub}SHOWNEWDATE=YES

 To  enable the date-divider graphic, ie what is shown when there is a date
 change  in  the  listing,  set this option to YES.  The text in the config
 parameter "NEWDATE.txt" will be utilized as the date-divider graphic.

@ENDNODE
******************************************************************************
@NODE TT4 "NiGHT-SCANNER v1.O Config Parameter - FILENUMBERS"

 @{b}Template: @{ub}FILENUMBERS=[YES/NO]
  @{b}Example: @{ub}FILENUMBERS=YES

 If  you  want,  by  default,  file-numbers  to  be  shown and want numeric
 flagging  available,  set  this  to  YES.  With this option, filenames are
 assigned 1 to 2 digit numbers, which makes for easier file flagging.

@ENDNODE
******************************************************************************
@NODE TT5 "NiGHT-SCANNER v1.O Config Parameter - HOLD.ACS"

 @{b}Template: @{ub}HOLD.ACS=[NUMBER]
  @{b}Example: @{ub}HOLD.ACS=200

 The  number  here will set the access level required for a user to be able
 to scan the hold directory.

@ENDNODE
******************************************************************************
@NODE TT6 "NiGHT-SCANNER v1.O Config Parameter - KC_NAME.[NUM]"

 @{b}Template: @{ub}KC_NAME.[NUM]=[TEXT]
  @{b}Example: @{ub}KC_NAME.1=BOSS-NUKE v1.5

 To  define  a new Key-Command you must first define a descriptive name for
 it.    If  you  plan to make a KC that calls a nuker, you should title the
 nuker  here.    All  KC_NAME texts (of KC's available to the user) will be
 shown  when  the  user  hits  '?'  at  the  pause  prompt.   [NUM] must be
 incremented for each KC definition you add.

 See @{" Key-Commands " link KC} for more info.

@ENDNODE
******************************************************************************
@NODE TT7 "NiGHT-SCANNER v1.O Config Parameter - KC_CMD.[NUM]"

 @{b}Template: @{ub}KC_CMD.[NUM]=[TEXT]
  @{b}Example: @{ub}KC_CMD.1=NUKE

 The  argument  specified here is the name of the DOOR that will be spawned
 with  Key-Command  number [NUM].  It will be called just as though it were
 written at the main prompt, with arguments if KC_ARGS.[NUM] is set to YES.
 
 See @{" Key-Commands " link KC} for more info.

@ENDNODE
******************************************************************************
@NODE TT8 "NiGHT-SCANNER v1.O Config Parameter - KC_KEY.[NUM]"

 @{b}Template: @{ub}KC_KEY.[NUM]=[CHAR]
  @{b}Example: @{ub}KC_KEY.1=X

 The  character  here  will  define  the key that, when pressed at the main
 prompt,  will  spawn  the  door  defined  in  the respective KC_CMD.[NUM].
 Please  note  this  character should not be 'Y', 'N', or 'F', as those are
 reserved for other prompt functions.

 See @{" Key-Commands " link KC} for more info.
 
@ENDNODE
******************************************************************************
@NODE TT9 "NiGHT-SCANNER v1.O Config Parameter - KC_ACCESS.[NUM]"

 @{b}Template: @{ub}KC_ACCESS.[NUM]=[NUMBER]
  @{b}Example: @{ub}KC_ACCESS.1=240

 You  may set the access level required to see/use Key-Command number [NUM]
 with this config parameter. 

 See @{" Key-Commands " link KC} for more info.
 
@ENDNODE
*****************************************************************************
@NODE TT10 "NiGHT-SCANNER v1.O Config Parameter - KC_ARGS.[NUM]"

 @{b}Template: @{ub}KC_ARGS.[NUM]=[YES/NO]
  @{b}Example: @{ub}KC_ARGS.1=YES

 If  the Key-Command number [NUM]'s door supports arguments and this option
 is  set,  the  user  will be given a large text field so that he may enter
 filenames/numbers  to  use  with  the  spawned  door.   If, for example, a
 Key-Command  activates  a nuke door and the KC_ARGS for that particular KC
 is  turned  on,  the  user may enter "1 2 3" and files 1, 2, and 3 will be
 affected by the spawned nuke operation.

 See @{" Key-Commands " link KC} for more info.
 
@ENDNODE
*****************************************************************************
@NODE TT11 "NiGHT-SCANNER v1.O Config Parameter - DIVIDER.TXT"

 @{b}Template: @{ub}DIVIDER.TXT=[TEXT]
  @{b}Example: @{ub}DIVIDER.TXT=*-----------------------------------------*

 The  one  line  text written here will divide file entries if the user has
 that  feature  turned  on.    The text should be less than around 78 chars
 wide.  Ansi codes may be used.

@ENDNODE
*****************************************************************************
@NODE TT12 "NiGHT-SCANNER v1.O Config Parameter - NEWDATE.TXT"

 @{b}Template: @{ub}NEWDATE.TXT=[TEXT]
  @{b}Example: @{ub}NEWDATE.TXT=*--------------< @THEDATE >---------------*
  
 The one line text written here will be written when there is a date change
 between  entries in the listing (if the user has the feature active).  Use
 the  text  @THEDATE where you wish the date to appear.  The text should be
 less than around 78 chars wide.  Ansi codes may be used.

@ENDNODE
*****************************************************************************
@NODE TT13 "NiGHT-SCANNER v1.O Config Parameter - ENDLINE.TXT"

 @{b}Template: @{ub}ENDLINE.TXT=[TEXT]
  @{b}Example: @{ub}ENDLINE.TXT=*=========================================*
  
 The one line text written here will be the last text outputted.

@ENDNODE
*****************************************************************************
@NODE USAGE "NiGHT-SCANNER v1.O - Usage"

 Check  out the "NS-USER.doc" file for information on actual program usage.
 The user may download this file by typing "N Z" at the main prompt.

@ENDNODE
******************************************************************************
@NODE KC "NiGHT-SCANNER v1.O - Key-Commands"

 Key-Commands  are  functions that YOU define, available to the user at the
 pause  prompt.    Up  to  8 KC's may be defined.  You may set certain KC's
 (such  as  one  that  calls  up  a nuker) to only be available to those of
 certain  access  levels.    You  may  set KC's that accept arguments, (for
 example a VIEWING key command, so that if the user types "V7", file number
 7 will be viewed.) Please consult the config file which contains 4 example
 KC entries. 

@ENDNODE
